                           <p><material key="marmor">Marble</material> 
                              <objectType>sarcophagus</objectType>, and <objectType>sarcophagus lid</objectType>: 
                              <dimensions><height unit="metre">0.95</height> <width unit="metre">2.07</width> <depth unit="metre">0.67</depth></dimensions>. 
                              Low plain ‘roof’ lid with four unworked bosses for 
                              akroteria; in the pediments small phialai; the chest has a tall upper lip and a laurel-pattern lower border; front and sides framed by narrow fluted pilasters with capitals 
                              and bases; on the front a rectangular tabula, held by two small Erotes; left and right of the tabula narrow garland swags from which bunches of grapes are hanging; 
                              within the two swags a young Dionysos and a satyr with a pine-wreath; on the short sides a narrow garland swag with a long-horned Pan mask and a stern Silenus. </p>
                        </support>
                     </supportDesc>
