         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" source="#chaniotisrrrs2016">
            <p>
               (Made while still) alive. This sarcophagus and the niche underneath it together with the platform belong to Aurelia Apphia, daughter of Attalos Amyntianos, son of Artemidoros; 
               in this sarcophagus shall be buried the aforementioned Apphia, alone. No one shall have authorisation to bury inside 
               another body, for he shall pay to the most sacred treasury 3500 -, one-third of which shall belong to the prosecutor. 
               In the niche shall be buried Aurelia Tatia, her alumna, alone. No one shall have  authorisation to bury any other body or to remove a body, 
               for he shall be subject to the same fine. A copy of this inscription has been deposited in the registry under the stephanophorate of 
               Attalis for the 12th time, in the month of Kaisar. I, Aurelia Apphias, daughter of Attalos deposited this.</p>
         </div>
